reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love how many plugs this has love that it has a C and USB plugs without having to use a block. Enjoy that it is flat and I can plug it up behind a dresser. Great length of cord.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars We have come a long way with power strips, another "why didn't I do this sooner" purchase.
reviews.reviewText: I'm usually a very early adapter to new techie things, but they always seem to be the things that are on the OTHER end of the power cord. All these new fancy-dancy tech items plugged in to....my 20 year old, computer beige (now yellowing) clunky, thick, awkward to handle power strips. You know the ones. I had to rearrange a desk one day and started unplugging things. I stopped and pondered a bit gazing at its out-dated ugliness and immediately set myself on a mission to finally upgrade. I didn't even know what was out there currently, so to the internet I go to discover I've been living under a rock regarding advances in power strips.This one caught my eye immediately for its compactness. I saw others that were the "tower" type, but I wasn't looking for a tabletop version. This one lays nicely on the floor where power strip belong. The braided and flat 10 ft cord is beefy but not stiff, so it is very easy to manage, and the right angle flat plug is GREAT for tight spaces. What I appreciate the most is the amount of ports on this tiny little unit, eliminating the need to plug in power bricks to power my charging devices, and they charge FAST.When I search for products to purchase, I do not only look at ratings on the specific item, I dive in to the sellers other offerings and review those ratings. It appears this brand is highly rated for there quality, and there prices seem very reasonable for what you get.I have a few of the ancient power strips in my home, that will soon all be replaced with this brand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact and Perfect for Traveling or Home!
reviews.reviewText: There have been many times when we go on trips and some of the places we stay don't have enough outlets for our phones, watches, etc., or they're inconveniently located elsewhere, so this was the perfect item to get, especially for the price.I've used this on at least a few trips and still works fine and now we don't have to bring our big, long surge protector or have to get up from the bed to an outlet on the wall. It holds 3 outlets and even has 4 USB ports, 2 of the slots for a type C port.It is high quality, durable and compact, so it doesn't take up much space either. Other than using it for traveling needs, this can also be used in the home or even in the office, making organization of so many wires hanging everywhere even easier.
